Die Lieferung erfolgt gemäß den Angaben in der jeweiligen Artikelbeschreibung. Dabei beginnt die Frist für die Lieferung im Falle der Zahlung per Vorkasse am Tag nach Zahlungsauftrag an die mit der Überweisung beauftragte Bank und bei allen anderen Zahlungsarten am Tag nach Vertragsschluss zu laufen. Fällt das Fristende auf einen Samstag, Sonntag oder gesetzlichen Feiertag am Lieferort, so endet die Frist am nächsten Werktag. (2) Die Gefahr des zufälligen Untergangs und der zufälligen Verschlechterung der verkauften Sache geht auch beim Versendungskauf erst mit der Übergabe der Sache an den Käufer auf diesen über.§5 EigentumsvorbehaltWir behalten uns das Eigentum an der Ware bis zur vollständigen Bezahlung des Kaufpreises vor.§6 GewährleistungEs gelten die gesetzlichen Gewährleistungsregelungen.§7 Vertragssprache§8 Umtausch & Rückgabe Nach dem konkreten Wortlaut des § 312 g Abs. 2 Nr. 1 BGB besteht das gesetzliche Widerrufsrecht nicht bei Verträgenzur Lieferung von Waren, die nicht vorgefertigt sind und für deren Herstellung eine individuelle Auswahl oder Bestimmung durch den Verbraucher maßgeblich ist oder die eindeutig auf die persönlichen Bedürfnisse des Verbrauchers zugeschnitten sind.Als Vertragssprache steht ausschließlich Deutsch zur Verfügung.Stand der AGB Nov.2020Freue mich auf euren Besuch

name: Atmospheric, torchlike lamp handmade from glass, wood and wrought iron.
description: This elegant assembly of glass, copper, iron and wood creates a jawdropping lamp, be it in bright daylight or at night. The design, inspired by a torch, is dynamic and extensive - optically filling a whole wall with ease. It can turn the bedroom to a more romantic place for love, brighten the eyes of your children or just make sitting together on the patio even more delightful. The images in this listing show the prototype of the lamp. I will produce the lamp you order especially for you, and therefore do ask you for communicating your personal wishes regarding details like coloring. The lamp you order will not look a 100% like the prototype, as it is handmade and suspect to small variation in style. Especially the lampshade, puzzled together in tedious and careful work, will differ in it's detail. It is made from rests of stained glass, on the inside cleverly placed mirrorshards channel the light for perfect dispersion. The copper, which unites glass and wood, can be either polished and sealed or left blank (which will lead to patina over time). I gathered this material from an old roof gutter.   The slightly singed wood resembles elegantly falling fabric. The sideward movement of the fire is compensated with the counterrotating wrought iron. To hang the lamp on the wall you need two screws, and depending on the type of the wall, other mounting material. If you wish I will send the lamp with a "SchuKo"-plug; otherwise the blank cables can be linked directly to your grid. !IMPORTANT INFORMATION!: If you do not have the knowledge to safely install this lamp, please ask an electrician for help.The main image consists of two separate images, blended together for reasons of clearness and illustration. It does not show how the lamp actually will look like when installed and switched on.

name: Mushroom-ish ear stud made from ebony and epoxy resin
description: These two studs are made from an offcut of ebony. A guitar maker could not use it anymore for making the guitar neck because of a crack that formed in the wood. For small pieces this does not matter, so I started carving, polishing and oiling the ebony, bringing out it's noble black lustre, keeping the small panes of the carving charmingly visible. As the epoxy resin penetrates the earring completely, the sunlight can pass trough to create appealing highlights. The resin is dyed with light-resistant tusche. These earrings resemble real mushrooms, quite fancy ones though - be it, like on the pictures, in nature, be it attached to you. The plug itself is made from stainless steel. The ear lobe is in contact with a small piece of leather. This is to avoid eventual allergic reactions that could occur on skin contact with glue.

name: Nature-inspired pendant "Talon"
description: A pendant, looking almost like the talon of a bird, or maybe a griffin ? Without hurting neither the bird, nor the griffin. The claws are made from bone, the rest from recycled copper. The copper ranges between polished and colourfully tinted by heat and oxidation, ranging from green to blue and purple, and being rough with a patina, resembling very closely real, harsh skin. The pendant is protected with matt varnish. This does not only feel like silk on touch, but also ensures the copper will not change. Even though the claws are quite pointy, you will not prick yourself. The points are bent slightly towards the center, pointing away from your skin. The brazen loop has a diameter of 4mm and is compatible with every chain within these measures. The bones come from a cow. I found them hiking in the Austrian alps and therefore am pretty sure that the animal had a nice life on meadows in the mountains. The copper comes from an old drain.

name: Four-tone hanging earring made of various exotic seeds
description: The euterpe oleracea is probably the most famous plant whose seeds are processed here. In Europe, however, it is more known for the edible part, mainly available as powder, and not for the hard seeds, which are often dyed into jewelry by indigenous people in various colours.In addition to the red seeds of the Falso-pau-brasil (Adenanthera pavonina), the black seeds of the Saboneteiro (to german walnut tree - Sapindus saponaria) and the white seeds, also called lagrima de job (Hiobstränen - Coix lacryma-jobi) they form the jewelstones of this hanging ear ring.Everything is held together by finely wrapped, silver-plated copper wire.I have picked up the seeds in different places in Brazil. Those of the falso-pau-brasil in the state of Cearo, the other seeds in different places of the state of Mato Grosso do Sul.You buy a pair so you can decorate both ears.

description: What started as a wet idea was, citing my girlfriend, "far to cute" to stay a dead duck. On demand I can also send them without any paint, but still polished.

name: Stylish and colourful leather belt with hand-forged buckle
description: A valuable and durable belt made from smooth, light blue leather. The buckle is hand-forged, partly made from an old chainsaw sabre. With adequate care this belt can accompany you for a long time, maybe even for your whole life. The leather is lightly treated with special wax. The vivid colour is perfect for emphasizing the features in the case of your clothing. I first made this belt for myself because I needed one who wouldn't fall apart. As it quickly found my friends' approval, I decided to produce another belt in a slightly thinner version to upload it. The belt has a width of 3,5 cm and a maximal length of 111cm. When ordering please let me know the desired length, and, if you wish, also the measures of your favourite belt concerning the holes. (This would be the distance between your favourite hole to the end of the belt on the side of the buckle). This allows me to accordingly prepare your new belt for it to feel just as good as your favourite, I can also produce a belt on demand, with custom width and in a similar style. Some pictures (the ones without the small ribbon-ish element) are from my personal belt, where I slightly failed the brand mark. Of course this did not happen in the model you will receive. ;)

name: Cicada with garnet beads as hanging earring
description: Often and for a long time I have been able to enjoy the chants of cicadas and other insects at night, but I have never seen their originators. Finally, two years ago, I found a tree with some dead cicadas hanging on it. I was very fascinated by the beautiful patterning of these insects and decided to preserve one of the cicadas.After some reflection, this earring was created, the cicada forms its center. With a thin layer of epoxy resin, I have made the in-house robust chitin even more resistant.The cicada is surrounded by shiny garnet beads, threaded on silver wire. She holds a small, hand-forged plug made of fine silver on her ear.

name: Extravagant bony octopus earring
description: This bone-carved octopus surrounds the earlobe with matt-coarse fishing arms made of fine silver, which run out in ends studded with grenade shards.The small sculpture also continues behind the earlobe by integrating the closure into the rear part of the body.The plug itself is made of stainless steel, the ear does not come into direct contact with adhesives due to small bone plates over the holes.The bone comes from Brazil, from a bovine animal living in the open air and died from unknown (natural) causes.When I returned from my first long stay in Brazil, one night before falling asleep, the image of this octopus shot through my head. Before that I had made a single stud plug out of wood, I had discovered the work completely new for myself. Without reading much about it, I decided to put the idea into practice and was very satisfied.In the meantime I would probably change some little things, maybe try to connect the silver without glue to the bone.At that time, an employee of the Pinakothek in Munich asked me if I would sell it - it took me three years to decide to answer this question with "yes".

description: On this stud the logo of the Finnish metal band "Insomnium" is emblazoned, as they used it during their first albums. This band I liked and liked very much, because it offers me both background sound at work as well as some support in difficult situations.The logo is sawn out of bovine bones; As with my other workpieces, these come from a skeleton found in Brazilian nature.The wood comes from an already quite eroded trunk, whose core still had the dark purple original color.In addition to the logo, a little brass powder forms a star, the plug is made of stainless steel. There is a piece of bone on the ear itself. This is used to prevent possible skin contact with adhesive.

name: Studs made of seeds of the Falso-Pau-Brasil and bone
description: The main component of this energetic stud is the red seed of the "Falso-pau-brasil" (Adenanthera pavonina). The robust and luminous seeds, along with many others, have always been used by indigenous communities to make jewellery and clothing, mostly in the form of chains. I collected the seeds in the state of Ceara.Did you know that these bright red seeds are often wrongly assigned to Pau-Brasil (Paubrasilia Echinata)? The seeds of the real Pau-Brasil (to german also Brazilian wood) however, are larger, brown, and resemble a very flat bean.The bone fragments come from a skeleton that I found on a pasture on a Brazilian plateau - the animal lived there free and hopefully happy until it died from unknown causes. When the bones were processed, there were leftovers that I didn't want to throw away - that's how this stud came out of it.The stud itself is made of stainless steel.

name: Spitzer stud earrings in polished Jatobéholz and glass
description: For decades, the grazing fence post must have been rife in the western Brazilian soil. Its very hard wood (Jatobé) was already far eroded, but in the core completely untouched by microorganisms and moisture. I made a hairpin and some tool handles out of the wood, but I didn't want to throw away the leftovers. This polished stud sare was made of the same wood, which impresses with its energetic yet simple shape.The glass is a melted shard of a wine bottle. The stud itself is made of stainless steel, a small piece of leather is attached to the earlobe, so that the skin does not come into contact with adhesives.

name: Necklace Triskele Triple Spiral Wood Burned
description: Unique men's or ladies wooden necklace.Triple spiral(Druidism): Derived from the Greek word "Triskeles" meaning "three legs", the Triskele or Triple Spiral is a complex ancient Celtic symbol. Often referred to by many as a Triskelion, its earliest creation dates back to the Neolithic era, as it can be seen at the entrance of Newgrange, Ireland. The Triskele gained popularity in its use within the Celtic culture from 500BC onwards. This archaic symbol is one of the most convoluted to decipher as symbolists believe it is reflective of many areas of culture from the time.1)The motion of action, cycles, progress, revolution and competition.2)Life-death-rebirth, spirit-mind-body, mother-father-child, past-present-future, power-intellect-love and creation-preservation-destructionIt’s thought that through the combination of these two areas we gain one meaning of the Celtic triskele. It is believed to represent a tale of forward motion to reach understanding. However, this is thought not to be the only meaning, as it is also believed to represent three Celtic worlds; the spiritual world, the present world and the celestial world. Like the ancient Trinity knot, the number 3 holds a special symbolism within the triskele.Material:Wood: Beech WoodCord:  Cotton Waxed CordVarnish: Odorless Wood Varnish for children's toysApproximate Dimensions:Size:  35mm x 35mm x ~5mmCord Size: AdjustablePlease note that this item is handmade, so there may be small differences comparing with the photo.If you have any inquiries, please don’t hesitate to contact me.
